WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.050
Ｔ Ｈ Ｅ
NIGHT AGENT
SEASON 01   #   EPISODE 03
"The Zookeeper"

2
00:00:06.050 --> 00:00:07.980
[BOMB BEEPING]
- Hey. FBI.

3
00:00:07.980 --> 00:00:09.470
I need everybody to exit the train.

4
00:00:10.390 --> 00:00:11.590
[PASSENGERS SCREAMING]

5
00:00:14.560 --> 00:00:16.560
That's him. That's the guy.

6
00:00:16.560 --> 00:00:18.640
[BOTH GRUNTING. STRAINING]

7
00:00:19.600 --> 00:00:21.440
[ ♪ OMINOUS MUSIC ♪ ]

8
00:00:24.860 --> 00:00:26.150
I don't know you.

9
00:00:26.150 --> 00:00:28.900
My orders are to protect you with my life. and I will do that.

10
00:00:29.860 --> 00:00:30.910
Housekeeping.

11
00:00:36.240 --> 00:00:37.370
PETER: Rose!

12
00:00:37.370 --> 00:00:39.040
[ROSE SCREAMING]
- [BOTH GRUNTING]

13
00:00:39.620 --> 00:00:41.250
We got some new intel on the target.

14
00:00:41.250 --> 00:00:42.880
Try to close this time.

15
00:00:42.880 --> 00:00:45.130
She saw you at the house and can ID you.

16
00:00:45.130 --> 00:00:46.170
This thing makes me ill.

17
00:00:46.170 --> 00:00:48.300
Maybe Secret Service needs to step in more.

18
00:00:48.300 --> 00:00:50.050
You stay on your own turf there. buddy boy.

19
00:00:50.050 --> 00:00:53.720
Did you know Hawkins used to be Emma and Henry Campbell's old FBI handler?

20
00:00:53.720 --> 00:00:54.640
What?

21
00:00:54.640 --> 00:00:56.600
I heard my aunt say someone in the White House...

22
00:00:56.600 --> 00:00:57.680
who couldn't be trusted.

23
00:00:57.680 --> 00:00:59.600
What else aren't you sharing?

24
00:00:59.600 --> 00:01:01.020
PETER: We found a hard drive.

25
00:01:01.020 --> 00:01:04.310
This has national-intelligence level security that I can't even get around.

26
00:01:04.310 --> 00:01:05.650
PETER: The metro bombing.

27
00:01:05.650 --> 00:01:07.860
What were your aunt and uncle doing investigating that?

28
00:01:07.860 --> 00:01:11.400
I don't know without being cracking it.
which I can't do without serious hardware.

29
00:01:11.400 --> 00:01:13.360
Hawkins called off her Secret Service detail.

30
00:01:13.360 --> 00:01:14.870
A farmer found him in a field.

31
00:01:14.870 --> 00:01:17.580
Somebody killed the Deputy Director of the FBI?

32
00:01:17.580 --> 00:01:20.160
Come in right now and bring Rose with you.

33
00:01:20.420 --> 00:01:21.380
[ ♪ MUSIC FADES ♪ ]

34
00:01:21.380 --> 00:01:34.380
Ｔ Ｈ Ｅ
NIGHT AGENT
SEASON 01   #   EPISODE 03
"The Zookeeper"

35
00:01:35.770 --> 00:01:37.770
[LION ROARING. SNARLING]

36
00:01:38.350 --> 00:01:41.480
Peter. Diane Farr. the President's Chief of Staff.

37
00:01:41.480 --> 00:01:42.730
Pleasure to meet you. ma'am.

38
00:01:42.730 --> 00:01:44.480
Looking good. all things considered.

39
00:01:44.480 --> 00:01:47.560
Could have been a lot worse.
- It certainly could have.

40
00:01:47.570 --> 00:01:49.440
Appreciate you meeting me here.

41
00:01:49.440 --> 00:01:53.030
The zoo lets me come before they open.
The animals keep my morning walk spicy.

42
00:01:53.030 --> 00:01:56.620
The last time I was here was. like. 20 years ago with my mom and dad.

43
00:01:56.620 --> 00:01:59.950
We spent the whole time arguing about what kind of animals we wanted to be.

44
00:01:59.950 --> 00:02:01.200
And what'd you pick?

45
00:02:01.200 --> 00:02:02.500
[PETER SIGHING] A bear.

46
00:02:03.160 --> 00:02:04.870
I was getting picked on a lot though.

47
00:02:04.870 --> 00:02:07.500
And nobody's about to punch a grizzly. I get it.

48
00:02:09.420 --> 00:02:13.130
So on the phone you mentioned you had a job you wanted to talk to me about?

49
00:02:14.840 --> 00:02:16.800
Have you ever heard of Night Action?

50
00:02:16.800 --> 00:02:18.140
Uh...

51
00:02:18.140 --> 00:02:19.600
Good. You shouldn't have.

52
00:02:20.560 --> 00:02:23.980
Night Action is a top-secret investigative program within the FBI.

53
00:02:23.980 --> 00:02:25.600
What do they investigate?

54
00:02:25.600 --> 00:02:28.020
[LION SNARLING]
- It's not my business to know.

55
00:02:28.690 --> 00:02:32.400
All I do know is that it always involves matters of national security.

56
00:02:32.400 --> 00:02:33.650
Eyes only.

57
00:02:34.450 --> 00:02:36.320
The operatives who conduct those investigations...

58
00:02:36.320 --> 00:02:38.280
are known simply as Night Agents.

59
00:02:38.280 --> 00:02:40.410
So you want me to be a Night Agent?

60
00:02:40.410 --> 00:02:41.330
[DIANE SCOFFING]

61
00:02:41.330 --> 00:02:43.080
God. no. Sorry.

62
00:02:43.080 --> 00:02:45.290
I want you to answer the phone for them.

63
00:02:45.870 --> 00:02:46.710
What?

64
00:02:46.710 --> 00:02:50.130
There's a secure emergency line in the basement of the White House.

65
00:02:51.050 --> 00:02:52.630
Officially. it's a redundancy...

66
00:02:52.630 --> 00:02:55.050
in case the FBI needs to contact the President...

67
00:02:55.050 --> 00:02:56.840
and other methods are compromised.

68
00:02:56.840 --> 00:03:02.260
In reality. if shit ever hits the fan.
a Night Agent can call that line for help...

69
00:03:02.270 --> 00:03:03.810
pass along a message.

70
00:03:04.640 --> 00:03:07.940
I want you to be the Agent on the receiving end of those calls.

71
00:03:08.610 --> 00:03:09.770
It's a dual role...

72
00:03:09.770 --> 00:03:11.820
FBI and White House.

73
00:03:11.820 --> 00:03:15.360
You'd answer to Deputy Director Jamie Hawkins and to me.

74
00:03:15.990 --> 00:03:17.070
But mainly to me.

75
00:03:17.070 --> 00:03:20.740
So essentially. I'd just be a glorified 911 dispatcher?

76
00:03:20.740 --> 00:03:22.530
The phone rarely rings.

77
00:03:22.540 --> 00:03:24.580
So I'd be behind a desk all day?

78
00:03:24.580 --> 00:03:25.750
All night.

79
00:03:25.750 --> 00:03:28.710
The opening is for the 8:00 P.M. to 4:00 A.M. shift.

80
00:03:29.420 --> 00:03:33.210
We need someone hardworking. trustworthy. loyal.

81
00:03:33.210 --> 00:03:36.840
Someone who does what's asked of them. who knows how to step up when needed.

82
00:03:36.840 --> 00:03:39.050
Like you did on the metro last week.

83
00:03:39.050 --> 00:03:41.510
If I'm being honest. it just sounds like a demotion.

84
00:03:41.510 --> 00:03:45.100
You'd be working in the White House. close to the real decision-makers.

85
00:03:45.810 --> 00:03:49.150
Agents who work the phone get their pick of assignments afterwards.

86
00:03:50.650 --> 00:03:54.230
Or you can wait it out in Surveillance.
hope somebody gives you a shot someday...

87
00:03:55.650 --> 00:03:57.570
despite your infamous last name.

88
00:03:58.820 --> 00:04:00.490
Seems like a pretty clear choice to me.

89
00:04:00.490 --> 00:04:02.580
[LIONS ROARING. SNARLING]

90
00:04:03.830 --> 00:04:05.290
If I am interested?

91
00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:10.000
You gave the wrong answer before.

92
00:04:11.040 --> 00:04:16.300
In the wild. sure. bear. lion. majestic. powerful. all that shit...

93
00:04:16.300 --> 00:04:20.550
but in here. they're basically just giant house pets.

94
00:04:20.550 --> 00:04:23.600
In here there's only 1 creature you should want to be.

95
00:04:24.640 --> 00:04:28.230
The one who decides when the others sleep. what they eat. who they fuck.

96
00:04:31.190 --> 00:04:33.060
The bitch with all the keys.

97
00:04:36.860 --> 00:04:38.860
Welcome to the White House. Peter.

98
00:04:40.110 --> 00:04:42.370
[ ♪ OPENING THEME MUSIC ♪ ]

99
00:04:43.660 --> 00:04:45.830
[HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING]

100
00:04:45.830 --> 00:04:47.120
[ ♪ OMINOUS MUSIC ♪ ]

101
00:04:47.120 --> 00:04:49.790
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]
- [INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

102
00:04:49.790 --> 00:04:51.460
Peter. did you hear me?

103
00:04:54.460 --> 00:04:56.420
We'll be at the White House in an hour.

104
00:04:56.420 --> 00:04:57.710
[PHONE CLATTERING]

105
00:05:00.970 --> 00:05:03.220
[DIANE BREATHING DEEPLY]

106
00:05:09.480 --> 00:05:11.140
[OFFICERS CHATTING INDISTINCTLY]

107
00:05:19.610 --> 00:05:21.400
[CICADAS CHITTERING]

108
00:05:22.780 --> 00:05:24.530
Hawkins had 30+ years in the FBI.

109
00:05:25.280 --> 00:05:27.080
He had a spotless reputation.

110
00:05:27.080 --> 00:05:31.040
It doesn't make sense why a guy like that would turn. I don't get it.

111
00:05:31.040 --> 00:05:32.000
Who gives a shit?

112
00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:34.000
Why did you tell your boss we're coming in?

113
00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:35.040
It's an order. Rose.

114
00:05:35.040 --> 00:05:37.670
You and your orders. Peter! Shuffle the fucking playlist.

115
00:05:37.670 --> 00:05:41.050
I'm not stepping into that White House and just handing over their drive.

116
00:05:41.050 --> 00:05:43.130
You can't get into that thing.

117
00:05:43.130 --> 00:05:46.220
You don't have the resources. The White House does.

118
00:05:46.220 --> 00:05:48.720
It could tell us who killed your aunt and uncle. Rose.

119
00:05:48.720 --> 00:05:51.770
And we could be handing over key evidence straight to their killers.

120
00:05:51.770 --> 00:05:53.770
I mean. Jesus Christ...

121
00:05:53.770 --> 00:05:57.360
the Deputy Director of the FBI was just murdered <i>Godfather</i>-style.

122
00:05:57.360 --> 00:06:00.860
So either he was clean and got too close to finding the actual traitor...

123
00:06:00.860 --> 00:06:03.610
which. by the way. is exactly what we're trying to do...

124
00:06:03.610 --> 00:06:07.030
Or he was dirty. and he was working with someone else in the White House...

125
00:06:07.030 --> 00:06:09.240
and they killed him to cover it up. I get it.

126
00:06:09.240 --> 00:06:12.040
Either of those versions sound like we're remotely in the clear?

127
00:06:12.040 --> 00:06:16.250
No. But Director of the FBI. Chief of Staff. the President?

128
00:06:16.250 --> 00:06:18.790
Rose. you think all these people have something to do with this?

129
00:06:18.800 --> 00:06:21.550
I don't know. And that's my entire point.

130
00:06:22.260 --> 00:06:24.670
I'm not going. and neither is this drive...

131
00:06:24.680 --> 00:06:26.760
not till we know who we can trust.

132
00:06:28.220 --> 00:06:32.430
When I told you that I was a nobody at the White House. I meant it.

133
00:06:32.930 --> 00:06:35.650
This is way above my level.

134
00:06:37.310 --> 00:06:41.530
We need somebody with actual power who can protect us...

135
00:06:42.190 --> 00:06:44.780
with actual resources who can get into that thing.

136
00:06:44.780 --> 00:06:46.530
That's Diane Farr.

137
00:06:46.530 --> 00:06:47.700
We can trust her.

138
00:06:48.740 --> 00:06:50.790
And you'd bet your life on it? My life?

139
00:06:51.790 --> 00:06:52.620
Yeah.

140
00:06:53.830 --> 00:06:54.750
Yeah. I would.

141
00:06:56.370 --> 00:06:59.330
My whole career. I've been kept down...

142
00:06:59.340 --> 00:07:03.010
because of something my dad was suspected of doing.

143
00:07:04.470 --> 00:07:07.680
Farr was the only one who never held it against me.

144
00:07:09.300 --> 00:07:13.180
She judged me on the merit of my actions. not my dad's.

145
00:07:15.730 --> 00:07:17.230
And if you're wrong about her?

146
00:07:20.190 --> 00:07:21.860
[CELL PHONE RINGING. VIBRATING]

147
00:07:26.360 --> 00:07:27.200
Farr.

148
00:07:27.200 --> 00:07:28.200
Hey. it's me.

149
00:07:28.200 --> 00:07:29.610
Peter. are you on your way?

150
00:07:29.620 --> 00:07:30.700
<i>No. not yet.</i>

151
00:07:31.280 --> 00:07:32.330
<i>It's Rose.</i>

152
00:07:32.330 --> 00:07:33.330
<i>Her aunt and uncle...</i>

153
00:07:33.330 --> 00:07:35.500
the shit at the hotel. and now Hawkins being murdered...

154
00:07:35.500 --> 00:07:36.410
She's just...

155
00:07:37.870 --> 00:07:38.960
She's a little jumpy.

156
00:07:38.960 --> 00:07:41.630
Can't blame her. Everyone's on edge over here too.

157
00:07:41.630 --> 00:07:43.380
Why was Hawkins in that field?

158
00:07:43.380 --> 00:07:44.710
<i>Was he gonna meet with someone?</i>

159
00:07:44.710 --> 00:07:45.880
We don't know yet.

160
00:07:46.720 --> 00:07:49.380
[SIGHING] It'll be the biggest federal investigation since JFK...

161
00:07:49.390 --> 00:07:50.760
and we don't know jack shit.

162
00:07:50.760 --> 00:07:52.640
<i>Director's briefing the President in an hour.</i>

163
00:07:52.640 --> 00:07:55.890
Hopefully we'll have more clarity then. What do you wanna do about Rose?

164
00:07:56.480 --> 00:07:58.270
All she needs is a good night's sleep.

165
00:07:58.770 --> 00:08:00.770
Give us till 10:00 A.M. tomorrow.

166
00:08:01.310 --> 00:08:02.900
DIANE: <i>Take whatever time she needs.</i>

167
00:08:02.900 --> 00:08:04.610
You still have the hard drive?

168
00:08:04.610 --> 00:08:05.900
Yeah. I got it.

169
00:08:05.900 --> 00:08:07.450
DIANE: <i>That's priority 1.</i>

170
00:08:08.030 --> 00:08:09.410
And be careful. okay?

171
00:08:10.570 --> 00:08:12.240
Yeah. I will.
- [DOOR OPENING]

172
00:08:15.240 --> 00:08:18.120
Hey. I know a place where we can stash the car overnight.

173
00:08:18.120 --> 00:08:19.830
Great.
- What'd she say?

174
00:08:19.830 --> 00:08:21.460
We have until 10:00 A.M. tomorrow.

175
00:08:21.960 --> 00:08:22.790
You ready?

176
00:08:23.920 --> 00:08:24.920
Let's go camping.

177
00:08:28.300 --> 00:08:30.130
MAN: <i>We believe he was killed elsewhere...</i>

178
00:08:30.130 --> 00:08:31.680
then dumped in that field.

179
00:08:31.680 --> 00:08:35.010
We've redirected every available Agent to solve this.

180
00:08:35.010 --> 00:08:38.350
So we have 0 suspects. even less evidence...

181
00:08:38.350 --> 00:08:41.350
and we don't know what Hawkins' connection was to the Campbell murders.

182
00:08:41.940 --> 00:08:42.980
Am I missing anything?

183
00:08:42.980 --> 00:08:45.610
No. Madam President. but we're working on it.

184
00:08:45.610 --> 00:08:47.650
Have you informed his wife yet?

185
00:08:47.650 --> 00:08:49.780
MAN: I told Cynthia a couple hours ago.

186
00:08:49.780 --> 00:08:51.570
Her reaction was...

187
00:08:52.780 --> 00:08:53.700
as you'd expect.

188
00:08:53.700 --> 00:08:56.580
Let me know when a good time would be to share my condolences.

189
00:08:58.830 --> 00:09:00.460
That's all. Thank you.

190
00:09:02.380 --> 00:09:04.210
[ ♪ OMINOUS MUSIC ♪ ]

191
00:09:11.800 --> 00:09:12.640
Diane.

192
00:09:21.770 --> 00:09:23.900
The Campbells' niece?
- Sutherland's watching her.

193
00:09:23.900 --> 00:09:25.980
And where are they now?
- DIANE: I didn't ask.

194
00:09:25.980 --> 00:09:28.820
It's safer that way. He assured me they'll be here tomorrow.

195
00:09:28.820 --> 00:09:31.700
Doesn't really feel like you've got control of the situation.

196
00:09:31.700 --> 00:09:35.320
All due respect. Michelle. you're not making my job very easy.

197
00:09:35.320 --> 00:09:38.700
Oh? Whenever you call me Michelle. I know you're pissed.

198
00:09:38.700 --> 00:09:40.410
I'm in the dark here.

199
00:09:40.410 --> 00:09:43.460
I have no idea why Hawkins would have pulled Rose Larkin's detail...

200
00:09:43.460 --> 00:09:45.210
because I don't know what Henry and Emma...

201
00:09:45.210 --> 00:09:47.670
were investigating through Night Action to begin with.

202
00:09:48.880 --> 00:09:50.760
What were you using them to find out?

203
00:09:52.050 --> 00:09:53.220
I can't protect Rose.

204
00:09:53.800 --> 00:09:56.430
I can't protect you. unless you read me in.

205
00:10:01.480 --> 00:10:02.350
Okay.

206
00:10:06.060 --> 00:10:07.860
Might wanna sit down for this.

207
00:10:08.900 --> 00:10:10.070
[ ♪ DARK MUSIC ♪ ]

208
00:10:10.070 --> 00:10:11.400
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

209
00:10:24.710 --> 00:10:25.670
[PETER SIGHING]

210
00:10:39.470 --> 00:10:40.310
Morning.

211
00:10:41.140 --> 00:10:42.770
How long was I out for?

212
00:10:43.390 --> 00:10:44.770
About 5 hours.

213
00:10:46.650 --> 00:10:48.610
[SIGHING] Did you get any sleep?

214
00:10:48.610 --> 00:10:49.690
No.

215
00:10:49.690 --> 00:10:51.110
Maybe someday.

216
00:10:51.650 --> 00:10:53.610
Somebody's gotta watch the cabin.

217
00:10:53.610 --> 00:10:56.530
I could have taken a shift.
- I didn't wanna wake you up.

218
00:10:57.620 --> 00:10:58.700
See anything yet?

219
00:10:59.780 --> 00:11:00.620
Nope.

220
00:11:03.290 --> 00:11:06.460
Look. I called Farr on her personal phone.

221
00:11:06.460 --> 00:11:08.040
I didn't use Night Action.

222
00:11:08.880 --> 00:11:10.750
Which means that if she's in on this...

223
00:11:11.300 --> 00:11:13.960
she could've traced the call and sent somebody after us by now.

224
00:11:13.960 --> 00:11:14.880
Right?

225
00:11:15.760 --> 00:11:17.470
Yeah. Okay.

226
00:11:17.470 --> 00:11:18.430
Thank you.

227
00:11:20.720 --> 00:11:22.770
So we're good. Can we go now?

228
00:11:26.100 --> 00:11:27.060
WOMAN: Help!

229
00:11:27.650 --> 00:11:29.440
Is anybody there?
- Get down.

230
00:11:30.020 --> 00:11:30.980
WOMAN: Please!

231
00:11:32.650 --> 00:11:33.610
Please!

232
00:11:34.900 --> 00:11:37.780
I fell on the trail! I think I broke something!

233
00:11:37.780 --> 00:11:40.870
The people who killed your aunt and uncle.
could one of them have been a woman?

234
00:11:40.870 --> 00:11:41.830
WOMAN: Help!

235
00:11:42.950 --> 00:11:44.700
[ ♪ TENSE MUSIC ♪ ]

236
00:11:44.700 --> 00:11:45.620
[WOMAN GROANING]

237
00:11:53.500 --> 00:11:54.380
Hello?

238
00:11:56.550 --> 00:11:58.380
Back wall. back of the cabin.

239
00:12:03.760 --> 00:12:04.680
That's him.

240
00:12:14.570 --> 00:12:15.530
Let's go. Come on.

241
00:12:17.530 --> 00:12:19.530
[ ♪ SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC ♪ ]

242
00:12:20.280 --> 00:12:21.160
WOMAN: Fuck.

243
00:12:23.830 --> 00:12:25.870
They're not in there. The woods.

244
00:12:40.470 --> 00:12:41.430
[ROSE GRUNTING]

245
00:12:42.800 --> 00:12:44.100
[ROCKS CLATTERING]

246
00:12:46.140 --> 00:12:47.520
[CROWS CAWING]

247
00:13:18.420 --> 00:13:19.880
[ROSE PANTING]

248
00:13:19.880 --> 00:13:21.510
Guess we got our answer.

249
00:13:24.550 --> 00:13:26.970
Always a tease with these 2.
- Let's go.

250
00:13:50.500 --> 00:13:51.860
Swap out the SIM card on my phone.

251
00:14:03.430 --> 00:14:04.300
Yeah. it's them.

252
00:14:09.970 --> 00:14:11.680
2-4-1-3-5-X.

253
00:14:12.180 --> 00:14:14.600
You got the license plate?
- Yeah. Yeah. I do.

254
00:14:14.600 --> 00:14:17.900
You're not gonna chase after them?
- Not with you in the car. no.

255
00:14:17.900 --> 00:14:19.860
Not when they outnumber me 2-to-1.

256
00:14:19.860 --> 00:14:22.530
I got the plate. I'll send it in to someone else to track it.

257
00:14:22.530 --> 00:14:23.950
Who. Farr?

258
00:14:23.950 --> 00:14:26.740
You need more proof that she's the traitor my aunt was warning about?

259
00:14:26.740 --> 00:14:29.080
I get how it looks. but I...
- But what?

260
00:14:29.080 --> 00:14:32.120
She was the only one who knew where we were. You said it yourself.

261
00:14:32.120 --> 00:14:34.500
I'm just trying to consider all the angles. okay?

262
00:14:34.500 --> 00:14:37.750
Occam's razor said there's only 1 angle. the conniving bitch angle.

263
00:14:39.250 --> 00:14:40.460
We don't know that.

264
00:14:48.850 --> 00:14:51.060
Thank you for protecting me.

265
00:14:52.810 --> 00:14:54.810
[SIGHING] Let's just get out of here. okay?

266
00:14:54.810 --> 00:14:55.940
Yeah.

267
00:15:09.070 --> 00:15:09.910
BEN: Diane.

268
00:15:11.160 --> 00:15:13.660
Where are Sutherland and Rose Larkin?

269
00:15:13.660 --> 00:15:16.120
Why?
- Well. aren't they supposed to be here?

270
00:15:16.120 --> 00:15:17.040
Maybe.

271
00:15:17.040 --> 00:15:18.630
What the fuck is that supposed to mean?

272
00:15:18.630 --> 00:15:21.090
It means you need to give me a reason to trust you. Ben.

273
00:15:24.260 --> 00:15:27.590
How does a witness's Secret Service detail get pulled without you knowing?

274
00:15:28.510 --> 00:15:30.010
Without your Deputy knowing?

275
00:15:30.010 --> 00:15:33.310
I didn't catch that Hawkins had pulled my guys till after the fact.

276
00:15:33.310 --> 00:15:35.430
Now I'm trying to make it right.

277
00:15:37.310 --> 00:15:40.020
Sutherland and Ms. Larkin were supposed to get here earlier today...

278
00:15:40.020 --> 00:15:41.770
but I haven't heard from them yet.

279
00:15:42.270 --> 00:15:43.980
I'll let you know when I do.
- MAN: Sir?

280
00:15:43.980 --> 00:15:46.530
I have Agent Arrington on the line returning your call.

281
00:15:46.530 --> 00:15:48.030
Please patch her through.

282
00:15:48.990 --> 00:15:49.910
Much appreciated.

283
00:15:57.580 --> 00:15:59.420
[PHONE LINE RINGING]

284
00:15:59.420 --> 00:16:01.000
BEN: <i>Arrington.</i>
- Sir.

285
00:16:01.000 --> 00:16:01.960
How's Badger doing?

286
00:16:01.960 --> 00:16:04.670
At the gym. then heading to class. Art and Activism.

287
00:16:04.670 --> 00:16:07.630
What I would give for a little tedious fieldwork right about now.

288
00:16:07.630 --> 00:16:08.590
Rough night?

289
00:16:08.590 --> 00:16:11.550
[BEN SIGHING] <i>The shit hit the fan with the Deputy Director's murder.</i>

290
00:16:11.550 --> 00:16:13.640
FBI wants all the backup we could give 'em...

291
00:16:13.640 --> 00:16:15.140
which is why I'm calling you.

292
00:16:15.140 --> 00:16:17.100
I'm pulling Ramirez to aid the investigation.

293
00:16:17.100 --> 00:16:19.690
Copy. I'll need to swap some shifts. but I'll make it work.

294
00:16:19.690 --> 00:16:22.110
There's no need. I'm sending a replacement.

295
00:16:23.150 --> 00:16:23.980
Erik Monks.

296
00:16:26.150 --> 00:16:28.990
As in "Monks" Monks? I thought he got out after...

297
00:16:28.990 --> 00:16:30.990
He's been rehabbing. He's getting back to 100%.

298
00:16:30.990 --> 00:16:33.280
I was thinking I'd start him off with something easy...

299
00:16:33.280 --> 00:16:34.490
<i>out of the spotlight...</i>

300
00:16:34.490 --> 00:16:37.450
<i>so I figured the VP's daughter's detail was the right fit.</i>

301
00:16:38.750 --> 00:16:40.000
When does he start?

302
00:16:40.670 --> 00:16:41.500
Today.

303
00:16:41.500 --> 00:16:43.130
<i>I know. It's last minute.</i>

304
00:16:43.130 --> 00:16:46.130
I was planning on having him join you next week. but...

305
00:16:46.760 --> 00:16:47.590
[SIGHING]

306
00:16:47.590 --> 00:16:49.130
...extenuating circumstances.

307
00:16:50.220 --> 00:16:52.010
Not a problem. sir. I'll get him up to speed.

308
00:16:52.010 --> 00:16:52.930
BEN: <i>Good girl.</i>

309
00:16:52.930 --> 00:16:54.050
[LINE CLICKING]

310
00:16:56.430 --> 00:16:57.930
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

311
00:17:06.230 --> 00:17:07.320
ARRINGTON: Maddie.

312
00:17:07.320 --> 00:17:08.530
I'm late for class.

313
00:17:08.530 --> 00:17:11.150
I wanted to introduce you to a new member of the security team.

314
00:17:11.160 --> 00:17:13.160
This is Erik. Erik. Maddie Redfield.

315
00:17:13.160 --> 00:17:15.780
It's a pleasure to meet you. ma... Uh. I'm sorry.

316
00:17:16.700 --> 00:17:18.200
It's a pleasure to meet you. ma'am.

317
00:17:18.200 --> 00:17:20.830
ARRINGTON: Erik's been with the Secret Service almost two decades.

318
00:17:20.830 --> 00:17:21.910
You may have heard of him.

319
00:17:21.920 --> 00:17:23.750
He saved the last President a few years ago.

320
00:17:23.750 --> 00:17:25.750
MADDIE: That manufacturing plant in Ohio?

321
00:17:25.750 --> 00:17:28.380
You're the guy who got shot?
- Yes. ma'am.

322
00:17:28.380 --> 00:17:30.670
MADDIE: If Chelsea's good with you. I'm good.

323
00:17:30.670 --> 00:17:34.260
By the way. I'm going out with Izze and Daphne tonight.

324
00:17:34.260 --> 00:17:35.180
Where to?

325
00:17:36.220 --> 00:17:38.140
Some bar. I'll text you the deets.

326
00:17:38.140 --> 00:17:39.390
Gotta run.

327
00:17:39.390 --> 00:17:41.600
Oh. don't forget your panic button.

328
00:17:50.860 --> 00:17:52.570
She always forgets her panic button.

329
00:17:52.570 --> 00:17:53.950
Millennials. right?

330
00:17:53.950 --> 00:17:55.280
Actually. she's Gen Z.

331
00:17:55.280 --> 00:17:57.450
And millennials like me hate the label "millennials."

332
00:17:58.040 --> 00:17:58.910
Noted.

333
00:17:59.540 --> 00:18:00.620
Keep up.

334
00:18:04.880 --> 00:18:07.340
Only a few friends. no significant other.

335
00:18:07.340 --> 00:18:11.510
She's a double major. Poli Sci and Art.
so she's in the studio a lot. painting.

336
00:18:11.510 --> 00:18:12.420
Got it.

337
00:18:12.420 --> 00:18:16.140
We try to fit in on campus as best we can.
make her feel like she isn't being watched...

338
00:18:16.140 --> 00:18:17.180
every waking moment.

339
00:18:17.180 --> 00:18:19.680
Right. I'll ditch the suit.

340
00:18:20.850 --> 00:18:24.730
How'd a guy who saved POTUS get stuck
on the Vice President's daughter's detail?

341
00:18:24.730 --> 00:18:28.480
Physical therapy. It. uh... it took a while after I got shot.

342
00:18:28.480 --> 00:18:32.360
So I guess this is their way of easing an old man back in.

343
00:18:33.030 --> 00:18:36.370
And every assignment is important. right?

344
00:18:37.570 --> 00:18:39.990
How'd someone so young get to run their own detail?

345
00:18:39.990 --> 00:18:43.580
I'm 28. but I can look younger. so I fit in on campus.

346
00:18:43.580 --> 00:18:44.540
Still...

347
00:18:44.540 --> 00:18:47.420
That's how Maddie wants it. She doesn't trust many people.

348
00:18:47.420 --> 00:18:48.750
But she trusts you.

349
00:18:51.420 --> 00:18:53.090
[ ♪ TENSE MUSIC ♪ ]

350
00:18:55.970 --> 00:18:58.430
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

351
00:19:01.640 --> 00:19:02.640
Go for Jenkins.

352
00:19:02.640 --> 00:19:04.930
Cisco. what's up. brother? It's Peter.

353
00:19:04.940 --> 00:19:07.980
Petey. You're up past your bedtime.

354
00:19:07.980 --> 00:19:10.190
<i>New number?</i>
- It's. uh... it's temporary.

355
00:19:10.190 --> 00:19:11.520
But do you have a minute?

356
00:19:11.530 --> 00:19:15.070
I need you to run a BOLO on a gray Ford Bronco for me.

357
00:19:15.070 --> 00:19:16.110
You're on an op?

358
00:19:16.110 --> 00:19:18.530
Yeah. but can't tell you anything else. man. Sorry.

359
00:19:18.530 --> 00:19:19.950
Good for you. brother.

360
00:19:20.530 --> 00:19:23.160
About goddamn time they let your ass out of the basement.

361
00:19:24.200 --> 00:19:26.160
All right. what's the license plate?

362
00:19:26.170 --> 00:19:30.040
PETER: Foxtrot. Zulu. 4-1-3-5. X-ray.

363
00:19:31.040 --> 00:19:31.920
Yeah.

364
00:19:32.550 --> 00:19:35.460
Yeah. I gotta get a new burner. but. um. I'll call you tomorrow.

365
00:19:35.470 --> 00:19:38.510
I appreciate everything. man. I owe you one. Seriously.

366
00:19:39.510 --> 00:19:40.350
Thanks. dude.

367
00:19:41.810 --> 00:19:43.220
Shower?
- PETER: Yeah.

368
00:19:43.220 --> 00:19:46.390
Thank you.
- Sorry about Farr. I know you liked her.

369
00:19:46.390 --> 00:19:50.190
If it really is her behind all this. I don't know how I didn't see it.

370
00:19:50.190 --> 00:19:51.690
What does that say about me?

371
00:19:52.690 --> 00:19:54.780
Maybe it says you wanna see the good in people...

372
00:19:54.780 --> 00:19:57.030
'cause you hope people will see the good in you.

373
00:19:57.610 --> 00:19:59.780
Not my fault you're so easy to read.

374
00:19:59.780 --> 00:20:00.740
Fuck me.

375
00:20:01.830 --> 00:20:06.250
Okay. let's say Farr is not involved. totally innocent.

376
00:20:06.830 --> 00:20:09.620
That means someone had access to her call log...

377
00:20:09.630 --> 00:20:10.920
and tracked us from your phone.

378
00:20:10.920 --> 00:20:12.210
Yeah.

379
00:20:12.210 --> 00:20:14.380
So we can't trust her to keep the hard drive safe...

380
00:20:14.380 --> 00:20:16.260
from whoever's trying to kill us...

381
00:20:16.260 --> 00:20:18.840
not until we crack it. figure out who Osprey is...

382
00:20:18.840 --> 00:20:20.930
and what's happening in. what. 5 days now?

383
00:20:21.550 --> 00:20:22.760
Well. how do we do that?

384
00:20:22.760 --> 00:20:27.520
Well. the drive's encryption algorithm's
too sophisticated to crack on my laptop...

385
00:20:27.520 --> 00:20:30.900
so I'm gonna need a beast of a computer.

386
00:20:30.900 --> 00:20:33.270
Like the CIA and NSA have at the White House.

387
00:20:34.360 --> 00:20:37.320
What. they didn't have any super computers for sale inside?

388
00:20:38.450 --> 00:20:39.860
Someone bought the last one.

389
00:20:39.860 --> 00:20:42.490
[PETER CHUCKLING]
- ROSE: Did get a burner phone though.

390
00:20:42.490 --> 00:20:45.580
Well. we're an hour past my deadline with Farr...

391
00:20:45.580 --> 00:20:48.540
so if I don't check in soon. that'll raise a red flag.

392
00:20:50.040 --> 00:20:53.670
On 2ⁿᵈ thought. what if we do give her the drive?

393
00:20:53.670 --> 00:20:54.750
What do you mean?

394
00:20:56.840 --> 00:20:59.510
So... I hate it here.

395
00:21:00.760 --> 00:21:01.590
Here where?

396
00:21:02.340 --> 00:21:03.850
This shitty motel...

397
00:21:04.350 --> 00:21:05.810
this depressing room.

398
00:21:05.810 --> 00:21:07.680
Nothing good's happened since we checked in.

399
00:21:08.270 --> 00:21:10.850
It's bad luck.
- Oh. you can't control luck.

400
00:21:10.850 --> 00:21:11.770
Sure you can.

401
00:21:11.770 --> 00:21:14.440
No. you can't. That's why they call it luck.

402
00:21:15.440 --> 00:21:16.280
Okay.

403
00:21:17.230 --> 00:21:19.740
But you can control your surroundings.

404
00:21:20.240 --> 00:21:21.570
It's basic feng shui.

405
00:21:22.160 --> 00:21:25.910
The happier you are where you live. the more productive you are.

406
00:21:25.910 --> 00:21:27.830
And this place sucks feng shui ass.

407
00:21:29.330 --> 00:21:31.080
[LIQUID SPLASHING]
- MAN: Okay.

408
00:21:32.420 --> 00:21:33.870
I'll find us a different one. then?

409
00:21:33.880 --> 00:21:35.460
Mm-mm. No.

410
00:21:36.380 --> 00:21:37.670
No more motel rooms.

411
00:21:38.380 --> 00:21:39.920
We deserve something better.

412
00:21:40.970 --> 00:21:41.880
A home.

413
00:21:43.220 --> 00:21:45.930
Why does it feel like you have something specific in mind?

414
00:21:50.390 --> 00:21:52.390
[ ♪ SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC ♪ ]

415
00:21:58.650 --> 00:22:00.900
[SIGHING] So are we doing this or...?

416
00:22:00.900 --> 00:22:03.740
There's gotta be another way.
- We need NSA-level shit.

417
00:22:03.740 --> 00:22:05.070
Kind of limits our options.

418
00:22:06.620 --> 00:22:08.410
Don't tell me you're having moral quandaries.

419
00:22:08.410 --> 00:22:10.200
Well. what. you're not?

420
00:22:10.200 --> 00:22:12.330
No. The 1ˢᵗ time I shoplifted. I was 8.

421
00:22:12.330 --> 00:22:13.250
Touching.

422
00:22:13.250 --> 00:22:15.000
Well. my mom ran off to some casino...

423
00:22:15.000 --> 00:22:17.340
with her flavor of the month for the long weekend...

424
00:22:17.340 --> 00:22:20.130
and I had just finished my last jar of Jif on day 1.

425
00:22:20.130 --> 00:22:22.920
I stole a packet of Flamin' Hot Cheetos from the 7-Eleven.

426
00:22:22.920 --> 00:22:25.300
I felt so ashamed afterward. I threw the whole thing up.

427
00:22:25.300 --> 00:22:26.640
Where is this story going. Rose?

428
00:22:26.640 --> 00:22:30.140
Well. the next day I went back. I boosted a Kit Kat and a Cherry Coke...

429
00:22:30.140 --> 00:22:32.020
and I kept those down no problem.

430
00:22:32.020 --> 00:22:33.310
I'm happy for you. okay?

431
00:22:33.310 --> 00:22:35.390
But I never picked up the habit of petty theft. so...

432
00:22:35.400 --> 00:22:37.520
Oh. you missed out. Risk and reward.

433
00:22:37.520 --> 00:22:40.110
Taught me everything I needed to know about working in big tech.

434
00:22:40.110 --> 00:22:41.940
When people think you're the son of a traitor...

435
00:22:41.940 --> 00:22:43.940
and all you wanna do is be in the FBI...

436
00:22:43.950 --> 00:22:46.070
you don't have the luxury of doing shit like that.

437
00:22:47.950 --> 00:22:49.160
This plan of yours...

438
00:22:50.040 --> 00:22:50.870
if I get caught...

439
00:22:51.950 --> 00:22:55.210
if any of it goes wrong. if we're wrong about any of it...

440
00:22:56.500 --> 00:22:57.420
I'm done.

441
00:22:58.540 --> 00:22:59.460
I get it.

442
00:22:59.960 --> 00:23:03.630
Even the slightest notion of disobeying authority feels wrong to you.

443
00:23:03.630 --> 00:23:06.090
But when it's your actual life at stake...

444
00:23:06.590 --> 00:23:08.260
that guilt goes away real quick.

445
00:23:09.220 --> 00:23:11.220
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

446
00:23:11.220 --> 00:23:12.770
[CAR HORN HONKING]

447
00:23:12.770 --> 00:23:17.980
Yeah. okay. Well. if we get separated. we're gonna need a place to meet up.

448
00:23:19.150 --> 00:23:22.530
Yeah. a. uh. uh. meetup spot. Sure. Where?

449
00:23:23.820 --> 00:23:26.990
Okay. there's a place just east of Canal and Foxhall. right?

450
00:23:26.990 --> 00:23:29.070
It's a park. It's called Foundry Branch.

451
00:23:29.570 --> 00:23:32.700
Find the pedestrian tunnel. go through it. You'll find a pier.

452
00:23:32.700 --> 00:23:34.870
I used to fish on it with my dad when I was a kid.

453
00:23:35.960 --> 00:23:38.210
But make sure you're not being followed. okay?

454
00:23:38.210 --> 00:23:39.540
Watch for tails.

455
00:23:39.540 --> 00:23:42.290
Okay. I feel like such a spy now.

456
00:23:42.300 --> 00:23:43.250
[PETER CHUCKLING]

457
00:23:43.260 --> 00:23:45.720
It's kind of the family business. right?
- [ROSE CHUCKLING]

458
00:23:49.850 --> 00:23:52.180
Say it back to me. Where are we going if we get split up?

459
00:23:52.180 --> 00:23:55.890
Uh. Foundry Branch. take the tunnel to the pier. check for tails.

460
00:23:57.020 --> 00:23:58.480
Good.
- Okay.

461
00:24:00.310 --> 00:24:01.190
Be careful.

462
00:24:02.570 --> 00:24:03.440
Yeah. you too.

463
00:24:11.370 --> 00:24:12.530
Hey. uh...

464
00:24:16.000 --> 00:24:17.080
You'll be okay.

465
00:24:17.080 --> 00:24:19.290
Yeah. so will you.

466
00:24:20.380 --> 00:24:22.040
And. um. for what it's worth...

467
00:24:22.040 --> 00:24:25.260
I'm... I'm glad it was you in the basement who picked up my call.

468
00:24:34.100 --> 00:24:36.970
Beirut's moving to tomorrow. We'll have to reschedule Watkins.

469
00:24:36.980 --> 00:24:38.690
Texas 22ⁿᵈ Watkins?

470
00:24:42.110 --> 00:24:44.610
Jesus. Peter. Where have you been?

471
00:24:49.030 --> 00:24:49.860
Hey.

472
00:24:55.740 --> 00:24:58.120
Rose ditched me while I was washing up at a gas station.

473
00:24:58.120 --> 00:25:00.080
Luckily. I had the drive in my bag.

474
00:25:00.080 --> 00:25:01.790
Any idea where she is now?

475
00:25:01.790 --> 00:25:02.920
No idea. ma'am.

476
00:25:02.920 --> 00:25:05.000
We have a file on her since the attack.

477
00:25:05.000 --> 00:25:07.460
We'll run down possible people she might go to.

478
00:25:07.460 --> 00:25:08.590
Good. Keep me in the loop.

479
00:25:08.590 --> 00:25:10.720
Sorry to interrupt. Drive's clean.

480
00:25:10.720 --> 00:25:12.340
No spyware. no Trojans.

481
00:25:12.340 --> 00:25:14.640
I've started a decryption on the air gap here.

482
00:25:14.640 --> 00:25:15.930
How long will it take?

483
00:25:15.930 --> 00:25:18.100
5 hours. 40 minutes. give or take.

484
00:25:18.100 --> 00:25:20.060
Once he clears. lock the room to everyone's badge...

485
00:25:20.060 --> 00:25:21.940
except for mine and POTUS's.

486
00:25:21.940 --> 00:25:22.900
MAN: Yes. ma'am.

487
00:25:27.610 --> 00:25:29.320
[ELEVATOR BELL DINGING]

488
00:25:29.320 --> 00:25:30.950
Go home. get some sleep.

489
00:25:31.450 --> 00:25:34.200
Almora's got Rose's description out to the metro area.

490
00:25:34.200 --> 00:25:36.200
We'll get someone to cover for you tonight.

491
00:25:38.250 --> 00:25:40.500
No. I think I should be by the phone.

492
00:25:41.540 --> 00:25:43.750
When she was at the hotel. Rose called me on Night Action...

493
00:25:43.750 --> 00:25:45.710
so maybe if we give her time to think...

494
00:25:45.710 --> 00:25:47.830
she'll call again. and I can convince her to come in.

495
00:25:49.050 --> 00:25:52.680
Or at least. uh. ping her burner. and we can get her location that way.

496
00:25:52.680 --> 00:25:53.840
Smart.

497
00:25:53.840 --> 00:25:56.390
You're handling all of this really well. Peter. It's noted.

498
00:25:57.510 --> 00:25:58.390
Thank you.

499
00:26:03.980 --> 00:26:05.980
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

500
00:26:09.610 --> 00:26:11.400
TEACHER: Nice work. Eva.
- EVA: Thanks.

501
00:26:13.950 --> 00:26:17.030
TEACHER: How's it coming along?
- Maybe just come back later.

502
00:26:17.660 --> 00:26:18.660
Or never.

503
00:26:18.660 --> 00:26:20.450
[TEACHER SIGHING]

504
